      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">25.203</ph> Preaward determinations.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1603e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1625e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            For any acquisition, an offeror may request from the contracting officer a determination concerning the inapplicability of the Buy American statute for specifically identified construction materials. The time for submitting the request is specified in the solicitation in paragraph (b) of either <xref href="52.225-10.dita#FAR_52_225_10"
                        base="i1053971"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.225-10</xref> or <xref href="52.225-12.dita#FAR_52_225_12"
                        base="i1054180"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.225-12</xref>, whichever applies. The information and supporting data that must be included in the request are also specified in the solicitation in paragraphs (c) and (d) of either <xref href="52.225-9.dita#FAR_52_225_9"
                        base="i1053788"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.225-9</xref> or <xref href="52.225-11.dita#FAR_52_225_11"
                        base="i1054019"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.225-11</xref>, whichever applies.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1625e27">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            Before award, the contracting officer must evaluate all requests based on the information provided and may supplement this information with other readily available information.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
